# Specification Change Markers Workflow

Apply this when working in requirement specifications under `spec/requirements/*.md`.

- Accept inline change markers from the user anywhere in the document (Feature, Use Case, Story, Item, or free text).
- Supported markers:
 - `[[ADD]] ... [[/ADD]]` for inserted text
 - `[[REPLACE: "<old snippet>"]] ... [[/REPLACE]]` for targeted replacement
 - `[[DELETE: "<old snippet>"]]` for targeted deletion
 - `[[NOTE]] ... [[/NOTE]]` for implementation hints that must not remain in final spec text
- When the user says "implement", first implement code changes from marked spec content, then integrate markers into clean final specification text.
- Keep wording changes minimal outside marked regions; do not rewrite unaffected sections.
- Preserve heading hierarchy and status labels unless the user explicitly asks to change them.
- Remove all change markers after integration, so the final specification reads seamlessly.
- If a marker target is ambiguous, ask one focused clarification question before implementation.

## Required check before finish

- Scan changed specification files for remaining `[[...]]` markers and resolve/remove them.
- Confirm affected specification file(s) remain valid under `Feature -> Use Case -> Story -> Item`.
